Dr. John P. Holdren, the Director of the Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP), testified before the House Committee on Science, Space, and Technology to discuss the role and responsibilities of the OSTP. He explained that the OSTP advises the President on scientific, engineering, and technological aspects of issues that require attention at the highest levels of government. The OSTP also provides leadership and coordination of the research and development programs of the federal government, evaluates the effectiveness of federal efforts in science and technology, and provides budgetary advice on these topics. Dr. Holdren highlighted several areas of focus for the OSTP, including advanced manufacturing, clean energy, space, scientific integrity, STEM education, open government and open data, big data, public access to federally funded research, cybersecurity, national-security communications, and international collaborations. He emphasized the importance of science, technology, and innovation in addressing the challenges facing the nation and expressed the OSTP's commitment to working with Congress to achieve this goal.